race.description: Community Bank Dunkeld & District Maiden Plate
race.comment: SUZE SPRITZ (9) is a maiden galloper who hasn't raced since finishing 4.5 lengths back in fourth over 1200m at Pakenham six-and-a-half months ago. Fitter for two trials, placing most recently, and expected to feature in this easier contest. RODRIQUEZ (5) ran a much better race at his second outing last start to finish second over 1000m at Bairnsdale. Taking on a better field but he is up to the task. DOMESTIC BLISS (11) is a maiden galloper resuming today after a spell of six months. Closed last campaign with a ninth over 1000m at Ballarat, beaten 10 lengths. Fitter for three trials, placing most recently. PRESTIGE SINPEX (6) found just one better on debut, when a well-backed favourite, and while this is tougher he'll be better for that outing. HELOVAWIN (1) is finding the breakthrough elusive, beaten 5.5 lengths into fifth at his latest appearance over 1400m at Coleraine and has had the blinkers removed.
